            <div type="edition">
                <!-- transcription goes here -->
                <ab><lb n="1"/>Solo donato a <persName><name type="praenomen" key="Titus"><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan></name> <name type="gentilicium" key="Flavius">Flav<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">io</supplied></name></persName><gap reason="lost" atLeast="3" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName><name type="cognomen" key="Niceros">Niceros</name></persName> <expan><abbr>l<hi rend="tall">i</hi>b</abbr><ex>ertus</ex></expan> sibi <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">et suis libertis</supplied>
                    <lb n="3"/>l<hi rend="tall">i</hi>bertabusque <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">posterisque eorum.</supplied>
                </ab>
            </div>


            <div type="commentary">
                <!-- notes go here -->
                <p>The reading of the text is uncertain without more
                    information or the other half of the inscription but it appears to be a donation
                    freedmen, freed women and their descendents by Titus Flavius (cognomen unknown)
                    for a plot of land, used for burial. There are interpuncts after each word except after the last word in
                    each line. The text indents to the right in each subsequent line, so “Niceros” in line 2 is indented the
                    length of one letter and “libertabusque” in line 3 is indented the length of two
                    letters. </p>
            </div>

            <div type="translation">
                <!-- notes go here -->
                <p>"With the ground gaving been donated by Titus Flavius... Niceros, the freedman, for himself and
                    for his freedmen... and for his freedwoman and for their descendants."</p>
            </div>
